First Lady Melania Trump thanked the White House Historical Association for their support and dedication in hosting an event. She also took a moment to reflect on the recent hurricanes in Texas and Florida and praised the first responders and the American people for their kindness and resolve in helping those affected. Melania expressed gratitude to those who have answered the call to help and acknowledged the support and gratitude from the victims of the storms. She emphasized the importance of the White House Historical Association in preserving and telling the stories of the White House and its inhabitants. Melania thanked the attendees for their continued support and dedication to the White House and ended with a quote from John Adams, expressing her appreciation for being in the historic setting and her hope for honest and wise leadership.